The paper proposes a method for semantic segmentation of 3D LiDAR point clouds using an end-to-end architecture that efficiently solves the problem as an image processing problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) as it focuses on LiDAR sensors, which are commonly used in robotics applications. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes an end-to-end architecture for semantic segmentation. The use of learned features also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves semantic segmentation, which is a common task in natural language processing.
